{
  "stem": "12462.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They did, and Nuremberg became the first place where simultaneous translation was used on a very extensive basis throughout the whole trial.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He-- he had been hesitant because of his war service, which had taken him to many countries.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He'd been hesitant to commit himself to stay with Justice Jackson for any period of time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he had, I think, at the [? onset, ?] I would-- I can't possibly stay because of my needs to go back to Texas later than Christmas.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So actually, he stayed until about January 7 or 8 or something like that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he actually put in, himself, some of the main evidence on the accused organizations, on the leadership corps, the Reich cabinet, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then he, pursuant to agreement that Jackson had made much earlier, he left and returned to Texas and had a distinguished career there.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Who replaced him at Nuremberg?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was replaced by Thomas J.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Dodd, who later became a United States senator, and whose son is now a United States senator, Christopher Dodd from Connecticut.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Tom Dodd was a-- had been a-- a trial attorney and a prosecutor underneath Justice Jackson when Justice Jackson was attorney general, and he'd had quite a bit of experience with the Department of Justice and otherwise.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So he was a very experienced trial attorney.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was a part of the Interrogation Division at the beginning, just before the trial began and after it started.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the work he did so impressed Justice Jackson that he wanted him to be-- to succeed Colonel Storey.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Actually, by the time Dodd was made executive trial counsel, I had become temporary head of a new division called Subsequent Proceedings.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
